ce:section.ce:para:
Electrodeposition of nano-Au-Hist in the presence of histidine (0.01 M HAuCl4 + 0.1 M H2SO4 + 0.1 M histidine) at 0 V for 300 s (Au/nano-Au-Hist) resulted in the morphology of dendrite with different sizes of hyperbranched pine-like structures (Fig. 2
                        ). The dendrites, however, comprise the building units of about 18 to 40 nm nanoparticles. Therefore, the dendritic nanostructure electrodeposited in the presence of histidine has a hierarchical structure. The EDS characterization technique was employed to further study the formation of nano-Au-Hist layers on Au electrode (Fig. 3
                        ).
